Word Cloud¶

In [33]:
word_cloud_texts = " ".join(tweets)
max_words=100
word_cloud = WordCloud(
                    background_color='black',
                    stopwords=set(stop_words),
                    max_words=max_words,
                    max_font_size=30,
                    scale=5,
    colormap='magma',
                    random_state=1).generate(word_cloud_texts)
fig = plt.figure(1, figsize=(35,35))
plt.axis('off')
plt.title('Word Cloud for top '+str(max_words)+' words', fontsize=70,color='green')
fig.subplots_adjust(top=2.3)
plt.imshow(word_cloud)
plt.show()

Sentiment Analysis¶

In [34]:
# Define a function that creates Polarity score for each tweet text
SIA=SentimentIntensityAnalyzer()
polarity_score=lambda x:SIA.polarity_scores(x)
sentiment_scores=df.texts.apply(polarity_score)
In [35]:
# Create dataframe for the polarity scores
sentiments=pd.DataFrame(list(sentiment_scores))
sentiments.columns=['Negative','Positive','Neutral','Compound']
In [36]:
# Create a label for each polarity score
sentiments['Sentiment']=np.where( sentiments['Compound']>0,'Positive','Negative')
sentiments['Sentiment']=np.where(sentiments['Compound']==0,'Neutral',sentiments['Sentiment'])
